Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.57,0:00:04.61,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A 60-minute Detective Conan Special!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.61,0:00:06.51,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today's case is a bit startling!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.51,0:00:10.15,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}An impossible and illogical murder in a secluded mountain temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.15,0:00:12.05,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The eerie legend of the {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.05,0:00:15.55,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No matter how it's hidden, there's always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.63,0:01:40.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mountain cherry blossoms are so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.27,0:01:42.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, there are some on that mountain too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.37,0:01:46.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Someiyoshi cherry blossoms they have in the city aren't bad,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.24,0:01:51.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but the cherry blossom's true beauty is only found here in the wild,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.34,0:01:54.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,secluded away from civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.41,0:01:58.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a wet blanket...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.12,0:02:00.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You say something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.05,0:02:04.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was worth renting a car and coming all the way here, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.22,0:02:04.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.92,0:02:07.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say we take a picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.23,0:02:09.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, you two stand over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.56,0:02:10.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.66,0:02:11.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.90,0:02:17.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Use the timer so you can get in the picture too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.40,0:02:20.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure! Just a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.34,0:02:22.61,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}My name is Conan Edogawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.61,0:02:25.81,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the would-be famous detective, Kogoro Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.81,0:02:29.78,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And this is my childhood friend and classmate, Ran Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.78,0:02:33.65,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Eh? How can she be my classmate?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.65,0:02:38.32,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The truth is, I'm actually high school detective Shin'ichi Kudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.32,0:02:42.19,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yes. It all began on that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.19,0:02:45.06,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I went to Tropical Land with Ran,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.06,0:02:49.27,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and there I witnessed a mysterious organization blackmailing someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.66,0:02:51.00,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Man in Black\NVodka
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.40,0:02:52.44,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I watched Vodka, a man dressed in black,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.44,0:02:58.24,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}while Gin, another man in black, snuck up behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:02:59.80,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Man in Black\NGin
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.24,0:02:59.68,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I was knocked to the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.68,0:03:04.12,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and forced to take a poison the organization had developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.43,0:03:17.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}M-My body's burning up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.13,0:03:20.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's like my bones are melting!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.73,0:03:24.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I can't hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.47,0:03:29.78,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}When a police officer woke me up—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.78,0:03:31.34,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}my body had shrunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.34,0:03:34.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So all we need to do is find those guys
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.65,0:03:36.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and get some of those pills!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.21,0:03:37.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.72,0:03:39.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If they find out you're still alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.52,0:03:42.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll come back to take care of you for good!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.39,0:03:44.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This must stay a secret between just the two of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.89,0:03:46.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't tell anyone at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.66,0:03:48.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means not even Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.76,0:03:52.25,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This old man is Dr. Agasa, an inventor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.53,0:03:58.10,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In my shrunken state, I became Conan Edogawa
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.10,0:04:01.87,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and wound up living with Ran and her detective father,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.87,0:04:05.11,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}in the hopes of obtaining information about the men in black.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.11,0:04:08.35,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But he's a horrible detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.35,0:04:14.15,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so I used the Doc's Anesthetic Watch Gun to put him to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.15,0:04:18.95,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and my Voice-Altering Bow Tie to solve all sorts of difficult cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.29,0:04:24.36,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And that's my life as Conan so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.36,0:04:28.47,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}When will I be able to turn back to normal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.47,0:04:31.34,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh well. It'll happen when it happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.34,0:04:32.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheese!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.91,0:04:36.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we should head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.74,0:04:40.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like there's a shortcut up ahead, so let's take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.78,0:04:44.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about this, Dad? We're not going to get lost, are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.72,0:04:47.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be fine, don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.59,0:04:49.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.09,0:04:58.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See, I told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.43,0:05:01.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're not only lost, but we have a flat tire too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.33,0:05:04.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our fun trip's ruined now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.44,0:05:06.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.57,0:05:10.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what we need—rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:11.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.54,0:05:14.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 20 or 30 kilometers to the bottom of the mountain!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.21,0:05:15.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.98,0:05:19.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like anyone lives around here,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.05,0:05:21.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we'll have to spend the night in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.55,0:05:24.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to camp out in a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.92,0:05:27.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you fix the flat tire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.36,0:05:30.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.36,0:05:35.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two flat tires in one day—talk about bad luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.07,0:05:37.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where'd he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.34,0:05:39.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.07,0:05:41.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.07,0:05:43.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.41,0:05:48.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you so worked up about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.18,0:05:50.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.38,0:05:55.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}? What was that scream?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.89,0:05:58.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:06:00.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, where were you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.23,0:06:02.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't wander off on your own like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.39,0:06:05.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found a temple up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.66,0:06:08.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet someone lives there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.74,0:06:19.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, there is a temple there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.78,0:06:21.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.58,0:06:23.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's go check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:25.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.55,0:06:32.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a really impressive place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.63,0:06:36.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sandei Temple...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.83,0:06:40.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like our only option is to ask to stay the night...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.73,0:06:44.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Pardon the intrusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.54,0:06:47.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is anyone here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.67,0:06:50.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.18,0:06:56.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked you what you want here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.65,0:07:02.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it you're from a newspaper or television station?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.52,0:07:03.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.66,0:07:07.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This place is not meant for uncouth vermin such as yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.26,0:07:11.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we were just passing by when we got a flat tire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.26,0:07:15.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were wondering if we could stay here for the night...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.13,0:07:18.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You want to stay here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.34,0:07:19.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.90,0:07:23.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's a problem, we'll leave right away—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:27.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Why didn't you say so sooner?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.88,0:07:32.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had you pegged as reporters who came here about the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.48,0:07:34.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"The incident"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.29,0:07:36.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing of importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.86,0:07:41.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One night plus vegetarian meals is 10,000 yen per adult
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.56,0:07:43.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and 8,000 yen per child.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.50,0:07:47.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This temple also serves as a small inn...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.53,0:07:49.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,10,000 yen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.57,0:07:51.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take it or leave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.37,0:07:53.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's six hours to the bottom of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.64,0:07:55.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Walk if you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.54,0:07:57.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't said no yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.98,0:07:58.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.68,0:08:02.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we have our first guests in a long time!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.45,0:08:03.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.65,0:08:06.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't said yes yet, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.45,0:08:10.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take my advice. Stay the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.09,0:08:12.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On rainy nights such as tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.09,0:08:15.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there's no way to know where it may be lurking...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.19,0:08:16.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"It"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.39,0:08:18.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a bear out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.40,0:08:20.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.27,0:08:24.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not nearly as adorable, I'm afraid...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.67,0:08:28.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I refer to an ancient beast that prefers rain and darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.11,0:08:31.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and devours people's souls...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:33.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.41,0:08:35.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.88,0:08:43.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I thinking?! That name is taboo here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.19,0:08:45.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget what I just said!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.72,0:08:47.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.43,0:08:51.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.53,0:08:56.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to introduce you to the four priests-in-training at this temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:09:02.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Kan'nen. He has been here the longest and is like an older brother to the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.95,0:09:03.00,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Priest-in-training\NKan'nen (21)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.94,0:09:05.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleased to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.17,0:09:09.79,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Priest-in-training\NTon'nen (19)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.21,0:09:09.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ton'nen. He may eat a lot, but he's a great cook and strong, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.09,0:09:16.26,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Priest-in-training\NMokunen (19)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.18,0:09:15.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Mokunen. We leave all the carpentry work to him and his dexterous fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.19,0:09:16.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.72,0:09:23.73,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Priest-in-training\NShunen (18)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.86,0:09:19.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This here is Shunen. He came to our temple just this year
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.52,0:09:23.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and although he's a bit timid, his passion for studying is unrivaled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.03,0:09:24.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.39,0:09:28.69,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Head Priest\NPriest Ten'ei (71)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.26,0:09:29.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm Ten'ei—the head priest of this temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.63,0:09:32.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ton'nen and Mokunen, prepare our dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.84,0:09:38.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kan'nen and Shunen,\Nshow our guests around the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.04,0:09:39.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:41.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we're staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.88,0:09:43.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.08,0:09:45.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With the late fee on the rental car and the cost to stay here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.42,0:09:48.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't have any money for booze this month!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.19,0:09:51.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Sandei Temple's main hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.66,0:09:54.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly is impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.53,0:09:58.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say to having your own funeral services here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.63,0:10:00.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.33,0:10:02.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lousy priest...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.37,0:10:05.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This way, if you would...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.18,0:10:15.61,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Huh? Why does that room have a lock on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.78,0:10:20.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Empty...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:23.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, little boy! That's—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.39,0:10:26.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's just a small room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.19,0:10:28.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.80,0:10:32.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's one tall ceiling!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.73,0:10:35.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.83,0:10:38.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:40.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our meditation room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.97,0:10:44.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They used to lock priests in here who broke religious precepts
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.14,0:10:46.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to make them reflect on their mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.21,0:10:49.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder it's built so solidly...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.05,0:10:53.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And they covered the room with lacquer to prevent climbing out...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.35,0:10:57.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, why does this part of the wall have a different color?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.49,0:11:03.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fixed that after it was broken during the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.66,0:11:06.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Kan'nen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.73,0:11:08.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.87,0:11:11.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It happened before I came to this temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.97,0:11:14.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't know the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.11,0:11:16.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- But apparently the {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}—\N- That's enough, Shunen!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.51,0:11:20.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our visitors don't need to hear about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.28,0:11:22.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.55,0:11:25.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.12,0:11:26.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.18,0:11:28.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.59,0:11:31.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's right next to this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.89,0:11:35.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.53,0:11:36.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.86,0:11:43.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! The waterfall's so close!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.47,0:11:46.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.27,0:11:50.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! Some of the water's even flowing over the handrail!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.91,0:11:52.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.34,0:11:54.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,While there is a drainboard there,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:56.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you don't want to slip and fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.68,0:12:00.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Cherry blossom petals!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.42,0:12:05.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They fall down from the cherry trees above.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.59,0:12:07.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Elegant, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.23,0:12:08.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.93,0:12:12.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dinner should be ready by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.94,0:12:19.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Priests have an image of being stiff,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.14,0:12:21.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but you actually have lots of time to have fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.74,0:12:26.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Sometimes we even go to the beach during our breaks!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:30.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We take out the temple's inflatable boat and beach ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.58,0:12:34.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the head priest is quite fond of girls in bikinis!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.09,0:12:36.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.99,0:12:40.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, I've been wondering about it for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.06,0:12:42.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but what's the {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.39,0:12:44.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you hear that name?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.60,0:12:48.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me. I allowed my mouth to get ahead of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:49.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Head Priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.93,0:12:54.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just an absurd old tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.27,0:12:58.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On rainy nights, the ancient Tengu creeps into the village
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.41,0:13:01.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and uses its tremendous strength to smash into houses
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.91,0:13:03.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and kidnap their inhabitants.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.08,0:13:06.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It soars to the top of tall trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.55,0:13:12.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,hangs the corpses, and devours their flesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.96,0:13:18.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He kidnaps only young girls who have tender meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.93,0:13:23.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, girls just like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.50,0:13:30.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's just a legend, don't take it seriously!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.17,0:13:31.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.34,0:13:33.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.18,0:13:37.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not just a story...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.52,0:13:41.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was an eerie incident just like that, two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.92,0:13:42.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokunen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.92,0:13:48.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, why don't you ask them the details about that incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.33,0:13:51.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you are Kogoro Mouri, Great Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.90,0:13:54.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You might find something out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.47,0:13:55.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The great detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.67,0:13:56.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Mouri?!\N- Mouri?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.83,0:13:58.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Kogoro?!\N- Kogoro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.27,0:13:59.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.80,0:14:03.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only you could ever solve that difficult case!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.24,0:14:05.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please listen, Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.04,0:14:07.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago, a young priest—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.71,0:14:10.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.72,0:14:15.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten our promise to never speak of that incident again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.55,0:14:17.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Head Priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.12,0:14:19.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dinner is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.16,0:14:22.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Return to your rooms and get ready to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.70,0:14:30.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective. I will let you stay the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.84,0:14:33.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I want you to leave the temple early tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.57,0:14:36.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take it personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.37,0:14:38.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.63,0:14:56.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.09,0:14:58.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tengu aren't real, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.30,0:15:00.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.43,0:15:03.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think kappa and oni really exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.47,0:15:09.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tengu are the same—imaginary creatures invented by people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.98,0:15:11.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.01,0:15:12.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, the ancient Chinese
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.81,0:15:16.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,referred to shooting stars that made loud, thunder-like sounds
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.75,0:15:22.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as "Heavenly Dogs," or Tengu, thus the name.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.69,0:15:27.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In China, such shooting stars were considered unlucky omens.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.49,0:15:29.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those beliefs came to Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.63,0:15:36.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Tengu changed from strange phenomenon to strange monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.50,0:15:41.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For a little runt you sure know lots of weird things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.54,0:15:45.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I, uh, saw it on a TV show the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.94,0:15:51.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's nothing to be afraid of, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.95,0:15:56.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly, I'm not afraid of anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.39,0:15:58.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.23,0:16:05.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.40,0:16:10.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you get scared during the night, you can come sleep with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.34,0:16:12.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nighty night!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.67,0:16:14.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.74,0:16:16.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.14,0:16:20.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you get scared during the night, you can come sleep with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.74,0:16:50.51,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He kidnaps only young girls who have tender meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.51,0:16:55.21,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yes, girls just like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.86,0:17:07.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid Ran, waking us up in the middle of the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.63,0:17:11.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the big deal?! I can't help that I'm a scaredy-cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:13.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what do you think that incident was?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:15.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heck if I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.07,0:17:18.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't want to talk about it,\Nso it's best not to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.87,0:17:22.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As if the {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0} would actually appear...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:23.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.68,0:17:26.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.75,0:17:33.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See! You're a scaredy-cat too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.22,0:17:36.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Where'd you get that mask?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.15,0:17:38.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was hanging in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.79,0:17:40.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.83,0:17:42.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.16,0:17:44.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:47.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, Kan'nen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.23,0:17:49.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasant dreams!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.77,0:17:53.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have brought this! Now what do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.11,0:17:55.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have put it on in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.84,0:17:58.61,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now I'm wide awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.92,0:18:08.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Breakfast is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.89,0:18:12.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! We'll be there soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.86,0:18:15.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You look pretty tired, Shunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.86,0:18:19.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I was up late last night reading...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.63,0:18:22.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.34,0:18:31.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't get much sleep either, Mokunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.14,0:18:33.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No thanks to your screaming!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.81,0:18:36.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't get any sleep after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.48,0:18:38.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.48,0:18:43.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's nothing compared to Ton'nen, he hasn't slept at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.42,0:18:49.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the head priest and Kan'nen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.29,0:18:54.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't seen the head priest, so Kan'nen went to look for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.07,0:18:56.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably in a room somewhere downing some sake—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.51,0:19:03.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was Kan'nen's voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.11,0:19:06.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounded like it came from the meditation room!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.85,0:19:11.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.88,0:19:13.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.66,0:19:20.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Head Priest Ten'ei!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.06,0:19:30.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was this temple's head priest, Ten'ei.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.84,0:19:35.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He died approximately between 10:00 PM and 12:00 AM last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.14,0:19:39.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you were the one who found his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.58,0:19:40.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct, Kan'nen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.98,0:19:42.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.55,0:19:46.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't see him this morning, so I went to look for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.55,0:19:50.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I found him in this meditation room...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.16,0:19:52.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And by yet another strange coincidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.36,0:19:56.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the person who rushed here after the scream was—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.36,0:20:00.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I, Kogoro Mouri, Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.70,0:20:06.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was one extraordinary scream, Kan'nen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.40,0:20:08.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not nearly as extraordinary as yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.64,0:20:12.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You have really keen senses, don't you, Kan'nen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.28,0:20:17.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the head priest was hanging all the way up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.62,0:20:21.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me, I probably wouldn't have seen him right away...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.05,0:20:25.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That is strange, Kan'nen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.96,0:20:28.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't happen to already know
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.46,0:20:32.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that he was hanging from the roof, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.03,0:20:36.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing of the sort! I just—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.13,0:20:38.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only natural for him to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.54,0:20:40.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokunen...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.37,0:20:44.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The exact same thing happened in this room two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.91,0:20:46.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.68,0:20:49.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I was in charge of that case too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.91,0:20:54.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe the one who died was a priest-in-training named Chunen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.19,0:21:00.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And it was Kan'nen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Mokunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who found the body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.36,0:21:01.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.56,0:21:05.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It happened during the rainy season...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.90,0:21:09.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After coming into this room to meditate,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.83,0:21:13.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chunen tore a big hole in the wall and disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.64,0:21:15.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We looked for three days and three nights,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.44,0:21:16.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he was nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.78,0:21:18.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We assumed he had fled the temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.38,0:21:21.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and on the morning of the 4th day,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.05,0:21:24.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I came into this room with Kan'nen to fix the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.58,0:21:27.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When we happened to glance upward...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.39,0:21:39.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...there was Chunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, hanging from the ceiling!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.20,0:21:43.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this hole the same place that was broken last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.40,0:21:44.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.47,0:21:49.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At first, we thought that Chunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made it to escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.21,0:21:52.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but the door to this room wasn't locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.41,0:21:58.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and a local carpenter who came to fix the outer wall
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.25,0:22:03.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,said it would take an entire day for a person to make a hole that big!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.62,0:22:05.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said the only thing that could have done it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.76,0:22:08.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was that powerful and ancient beast...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.56,0:22:10.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...the {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.76,0:22:13.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.47,0:22:25.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous. There's no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.11,0:22:27.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.05,0:22:29.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It really is exactly like two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.51,0:22:32.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The two side beams are covered in dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.15,0:22:35.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and there are no signs of anything touching them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.19,0:22:38.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bit of dust has been knocked off the middle beam,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.16,0:22:39.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but that's because of the rope tied to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.93,0:22:42.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are no rub marks to indicate he was hoisted up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.73,0:22:45.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you suppose this was a suicide too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.80,0:22:47.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.27,0:22:49.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you can manage to get up there
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.20,0:22:53.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if you climb across the beams and use rope like that officer,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.57,0:22:57.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's a different story if you're trying to carry someone up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.28,0:23:01.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The late priest Chunen and the head priest weren't all that small.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.55,0:23:05.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Scaling the rope with them tied to your back would be nigh impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.98,0:23:09.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you tied the noose around their necks and hoisted them up,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.09,0:23:11.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would leave marks on the beam.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.66,0:23:15.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone could have climbed up first and then pulled them up,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.96,0:23:19.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but that narrow beam is the only place to stand,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.16,0:23:21.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it's extremely unlikely.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.63,0:23:24.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means they must have climbed the ropes themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.84,0:23:27.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,made a noose while on the beam,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.97,0:23:32.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then jumped off with the noose around their necks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.11,0:23:37.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Some leftover rope and an axe probably used to cut it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.58,0:23:39.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,were found on the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.38,0:23:41.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it would seem that was case.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.95,0:23:44.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what has me wondering is that hole in the wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.76,0:23:47.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...it's exactly like last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.39,0:23:49.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how they broke the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.59,0:23:53.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but they probably broke it and hanged themselves from a tall ceiling
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.60,0:23:58.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it look like that old legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.17,0:24:00.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost as if to suggest to us
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.07,0:24:04.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that they were attacked by the flying {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.84,0:24:09.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That ridiculous tale sends everyone in a panic...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.15,0:24:14.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't this broken wall seem strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.79,0:24:17.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a sliding panel here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.29,0:24:19.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.09,0:24:26.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For such a big hole in the wall, there's almost no debris left.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.30,0:24:29.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.03,0:24:31.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably threw them over.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.94,0:24:34.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, these people did make their suicides
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.27,0:24:36.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,look like the {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}'s doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.17,0:24:39.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows what they were thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.38,0:24:41.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.25,0:24:45.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.05,0:24:47.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Isn't she—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.12,0:24:49.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The head priest's granddaughter, Kikuno{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.92,0:24:50.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa! Why did this happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.42,0:24:54.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ten'ei's Granddaughter Kikuno, 21 years old" Grandpa! Why did this happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.26,0:25:00.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She cried two years ago too, when she saw Priest Chunen's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.60,0:25:05.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She used to visit on occasion back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.74,0:25:08.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but she suddenly stopped coming after the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.94,0:25:11.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.94,0:25:13.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's he?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.41,0:25:17.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kikuno{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.02,0:25:20.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They married only a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.19,0:25:22.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear he's the successor to a big temple
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.95,0:25:26.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the two of them were arranged to be married since they were little.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.56,0:25:31.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was really shocked when I heard that from the head priest two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.70,0:25:36.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had always thought that she and Chunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were to be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.23,0:25:38.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The late Chunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.37,0:25:39.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.40,0:25:43.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The two were so close they seemed like real brother and sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.31,0:25:46.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been a real shock to Chunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.01,0:25:49.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when he heard she was going to be married.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.05,0:25:51.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably why he did that foolish thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.45,0:25:55.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the head priest had been worrying about that this whole time—
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.52,0:25:57.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...and killed himself like Chunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.32,0:26:01.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,mere days after Kikuno{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wedding!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.13,0:26:03.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a possibility...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.16,0:26:06.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then there should be a will somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.26,0:26:09.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's all split up and look for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.67,0:26:14.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.27,0:26:16.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Are you so sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.27,0:26:19.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No matter how much it looks like the old legend,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.18,0:26:22.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}would anybody really hang themselves from a place like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.28,0:26:26.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And would they really make such a big hole on purpose?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.69,0:26:29.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What if it wasn't a suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.02,0:26:32.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and this big hole was used for some sort of trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.92,0:26:36.36,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This incident and the one two years ago were pulled off the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.36,0:26:42.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Meaning Chunen and the head priest were murdered by the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.47,0:26:44.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.94,0:26:48.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.94,0:26:53.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come to think of it, this guy said he came to this temple one year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.51,0:27:00.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I doubt he could've made that big hole with these scrawny arms...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.85,0:27:05.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, you said you were up late last night reading a book, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.92,0:27:08.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I was awake until a little past 3:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.83,0:27:12.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you notice anything strange during that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.60,0:27:16.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like anyone sneaking out of their room,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.33,0:27:18.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or an eerie sound from something breaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.77,0:27:20.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or anyone screaming?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.47,0:27:23.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.27,0:27:26.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Last night was a quiet night.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.21,0:27:27.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You really heard nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.75,0:27:28.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.58,0:27:30.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The head priest's room is a little ways away,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.88,0:27:33.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but everyone's sleeping quarters are next to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.15,0:27:36.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we'd know right away if anything happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.09,0:27:39.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're suspicious of everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.46,0:27:40.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.26,0:27:42.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shunen!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.23,0:27:45.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop lounging around and help us look!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.26,0:27:46.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.14,0:28:02.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, just a little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.45,0:28:05.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You freaked me out when you started to lose your grip there!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.32,0:28:06.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry 'bout that!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.42,0:28:08.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, officers!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.85,0:28:11.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the window at the top of the room
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.09,0:28:12.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where the head priest died, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.39,0:28:14.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.86,0:28:19.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't carry someone through here onto the middle beam?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.16,0:28:23.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it'd be impossible without leaving marks on the beam...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.67,0:28:26.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, it'd be crazy to carry someone in there
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.27,0:28:29.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and try to do things on top of something so narrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.28,0:28:39.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's with this drainboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.08,0:28:41.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The cut is warped!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.12,0:28:43.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The rest are just fine, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.62,0:28:48.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.23,0:28:50.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But the cut is old.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.09,0:28:53.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It was made quite a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.60,0:28:56.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There are cherry blossom petals stuck to the underside...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.97,0:28:58.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}How?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.94,0:29:01.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.51,0:29:05.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.04,0:29:06.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.64,0:29:07.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for that boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.81,0:29:09.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he asked how to get to the woods below the temple
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.68,0:29:11.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then left.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.00,0:29:26.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The only things missing from the scene
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.33,0:29:29.67,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}were the fragments from that broken wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.67,0:29:33.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If the killer threw them over the side,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.14,0:29:35.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}they would have landed around here somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.81,0:29:38.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If I can find them,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.54,0:29:41.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I might figure out the reason the killer had to get rid of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.65,0:29:44.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And then the mystery behind the killer's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.16,0:29:56.93,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Bingo! A piece of wood!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.93,0:30:00.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This was part of that sliding panel...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.50,0:30:05.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's tape on it... What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.14,0:30:07.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing down here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.94,0:30:09.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.61,0:30:11.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that dirty piece of wood?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.51,0:30:13.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get rid of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.38,0:30:15.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.05,0:30:23.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's call it a day!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.02,0:30:25.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.06,0:30:27.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, where's Kikuno{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.39,0:30:31.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She went with the body to the police headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.36,0:30:34.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't seem to find his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.70,0:30:38.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay. At least we know it was a suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.90,0:30:42.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No! It was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.07,0:30:44.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Something happened in this room last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.78,0:30:48.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Something beyond imagination!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.08,0:30:51.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The wall which was destroyed by an immense strength...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.45,0:30:53.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The warped cut on the drainboard...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.59,0:30:57.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And the dumped piece of wood from the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.12,0:31:00.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and the tape that was stuck to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.22,0:31:03.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What is the key that connects them all?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.94,0:31:15.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A cherry blossom?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.44,0:31:19.84,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's it! I've figured out the killer's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.11,0:31:25.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If that's the case, then the killer must've spent the entire night in this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.98,0:31:30.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah! So that's why he said that!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.25,0:31:34.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's the killer, no question about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.76,0:31:40.40,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The impossible crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.40,0:31:45.27,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...a work of foul art created at the scene of the crime by a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.27,0:31:47.64,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The piece of art exhibited this time
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.64,0:31:50.28,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}was a room in a mountain temple where the cherry blossoms fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.28,0:31:52.61,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Someone murdered the temple's head priest
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.61,0:31:55.85,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}by tying him to an elevated beam and then hanging him!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.85,0:31:59.08,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Naturally, there were no marks of him being pulled up.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.08,0:32:02.19,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It seems utterly impossible for a human to commit this crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.19,0:32:06.46,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yes, the killer utilized a certain technique to float in the air!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.46,0:32:11.43,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just like the adroit flying {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.43,0:32:13.63,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Some unused rope and an axe lay on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.63,0:32:16.30,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}of the room where the head priest was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.30,0:32:17.70,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But the strangest thing of all
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.70,0:32:20.84,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}was that although there was a huge hole in the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.84,0:32:23.78,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}there was no debris from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.78,0:32:26.65,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Then there was the drainboard with the warped cut,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.65,0:32:29.58,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and the piece of wood from the sliding panel
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.58,0:32:32.25,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and the tape that was on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.25,0:32:34.81,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What is the key that connects them all?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.99,0:32:41.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A cherry blossom?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.13,0:32:45.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's it! I've figured out the killer's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.06,0:32:46.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.73,0:32:49.84,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}then the killer must've spent the entire night in this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.84,0:32:53.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah! So that's why he said that!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.81,0:32:58.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He's the killer, no question about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.54,0:33:01.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Inspector Megure?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.31,0:33:03.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.22,0:33:05.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take you home in my patrol car.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.98,0:33:09.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I have to make them notice before everyone leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.62,0:33:12.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand over the keys to the rental car
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.32,0:33:15.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that just happened to get a flat tire in the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.09,0:33:18.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have one of my men return it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.00,0:33:21.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We owe a great deal to your detective skills, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.47,0:33:24.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks a bunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.90,0:33:26.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got the keys!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.87,0:33:28.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back here, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.68,0:33:34.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, where'd that brat go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.15,0:33:36.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No drainboards!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.95,0:33:42.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, he slipped and knocked himself out...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.86,0:33:43.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.72,0:33:48.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I don't have to use the Anesthetic Watch Gun on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.53,0:33:51.50,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This button acts as a tiny wireless speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.50,0:33:57.07,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Whatever you say into your bow tie will come out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.07,0:33:58.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll just stick this here...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.74,0:34:00.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.51,0:34:02.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.17,0:34:03.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't come in here without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.94,0:34:05.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.14,0:34:07.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said he wants everyone to gather in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.41,0:34:09.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where the incident happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.62,0:34:13.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And do you have any tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.52,0:34:15.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.55,0:34:18.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You know who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.62,0:34:19.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.42,0:34:22.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know who killed the head priest and made it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.96,0:34:24.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.10,0:34:27.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The head priest died after he was tied to an elevated beam
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.97,0:34:30.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and hanged!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.10,0:34:32.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're saying someone set that up,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.70,0:34:35.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,how in the world did they do it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.37,0:34:40.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no marks on the beam of him being pulled up, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.38,0:34:42.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course there aren't any marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.92,0:34:47.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer floated directly up to the beam along with the head priest
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.95,0:34:51.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then tied him to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.49,0:34:53.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Floated up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.29,0:34:55.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it was the {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.86,0:34:58.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No human could do anything like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.46,0:35:00.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hear that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.57,0:35:02.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's the waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.77,0:35:08.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The waterfall that flows directly next to the top window...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.07,0:35:11.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be possible to float to the ceiling
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.14,0:35:14.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if you diverted the waterfall through the window
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.48,0:35:18.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and filled the entire room with water?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.38,0:35:22.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fill this entire room with water?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.29,0:35:24.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to be kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.52,0:35:27.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Both the killer and the victim would be sopping wet,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.63,0:35:30.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but there were no signs of wetness on the body at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.90,0:35:32.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An inflatable raft, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.83,0:35:34.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An inflatable raft?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.97,0:35:35.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kan'nen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.93,0:35:40.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said there was an inflatable raft in the temple, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.17,0:35:41.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.57,0:35:46.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the body was in the raft and covered with a plastic sheet or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.68,0:35:49.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then it could have made it to the top without getting wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.92,0:35:53.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the waterfall and the window are too far apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.79,0:35:55.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how well things might fit,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.42,0:36:01.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,nobody could divert the water into the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.26,0:36:03.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The drainboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.40,0:36:06.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer covered the gaps in the drainboard with tape, flipped it over,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.77,0:36:09.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then redirected the waterfall through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.37,0:36:13.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof of this, the cut on the drainboard is warped.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.51,0:36:17.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was cut to make it short enough to fit...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.21,0:36:20.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And there are cherry blossom petals stuck to the board
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.95,0:36:24.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in the spots where the tape would have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.35,0:36:27.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The same petals that are carried down the waterfall
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.19,0:36:29.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,from the trees at the top of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.73,0:36:40.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And it wasn't just the drainboard that had flower petals stuck to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.13,0:36:44.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They should fall down to your feet soon, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.24,0:36:48.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The petals that got stuck to the side of the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.24,0:36:52.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when the killer removed the water, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.11,0:36:56.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, after killing the head priest,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.08,0:36:57.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer carried the body into this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.52,0:36:58.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,put it into the inflatable raft,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.62,0:37:02.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,covered the inner doorframe with tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.29,0:37:07.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and temporarily left the room through the sliding panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.16,0:37:09.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the killer began filling the room with water
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.13,0:37:11.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,from the second floor window using the method I just illustrated,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.40,0:37:12.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,quickly returned to the 1st floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.93,0:37:14.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,entered through the sliding panel,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.60,0:37:16.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then covered it with tape too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.60,0:37:21.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, the water would leak out through the panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.41,0:37:25.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, while taking great care not to get the body wet,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.28,0:37:28.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,all the killer had to do was wait for the room to fill up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.45,0:37:32.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After the room filled up enough, the killer arrived at the beam,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.45,0:37:34.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,tied the corpse to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.45,0:37:38.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then escaped out the top window.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.89,0:37:41.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But how did the killer get rid of the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.56,0:37:43.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By breaking the sliding panel with the axe
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.56,0:37:45.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that was left at the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.90,0:37:50.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. This room's floor is about 4.5 tatami in area
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.24,0:37:52.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the walls are about 10 meters high,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.40,0:37:56.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so its volume is 2.7 meters by 2.7 meters by 10 meters,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.61,0:37:59.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or 72.9 meters cubed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.75,0:38:02.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The specific gravity of water is 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.15,0:38:07.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so the weight of all the water in the filled room would be 72.9 metric tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.15,0:38:10.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you used an axe to break a panel at the bottom of a room
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.36,0:38:11.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with that much water,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.39,0:38:14.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you know what would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.63,0:38:22.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cracked panel would fly out under 9.8×10⁴ Pascals of pressure!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.43,0:38:24.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Under the immense strength of the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.17,0:38:28.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,more and more of the wall would erode off, creating a gaping hole!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.44,0:38:32.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,9.8×10⁴ Pascals?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.38,0:38:37.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A huge amount of power—\Nlike getting run over by a truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.15,0:38:38.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.38,0:38:43.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why there's no debris even though the hole is so big!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.96,0:38:49.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan found a fragment of the wall in the woods below the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.09,0:38:50.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He did?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.96,0:38:53.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.83,0:38:56.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.84,0:39:00.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of the sliding panel with tape on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.11,0:39:03.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But who in the world would do such a thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.08,0:39:06.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would take less than 10 seconds for the water to exit the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.45,0:39:09.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but filling the room, that's a whole different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.25,0:39:11.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The amount of water entering from the drainboard
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.25,0:39:13.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is 5 to 6 times as much as through a faucet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.59,0:39:17.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If we estimate that it filled up 10 cubic meters per hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.86,0:39:24.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would take 7 hours to completely fill this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.33,0:39:26.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The head priest's estimated time of death
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.80,0:39:29.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was between 10:00 PM and 12:00 AM last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.53,0:39:48.01,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Estimated Time of Death
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.70,0:39:34.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And it was 8:00 AM when his body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.28,0:39:48.01,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Time of Body's Discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.21,0:39:37.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you deduct the time to set up the trick
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.48,0:39:41.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the time needed to release the water and dry the room
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.78,0:39:48.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer must have been in this room between midnight and 6:00 AM!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.22,0:39:51.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that have to do with the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.89,0:39:54.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.06,0:39:57.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were reading a book in your room
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.36,0:40:00.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,until 3:00 AM last night, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.57,0:40:07.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then you too should've heard a certain someone scream
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.04,0:40:10.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when they saw the Tengu mask from the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.24,0:40:12.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who screamed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.81,0:40:14.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.91,0:40:16.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shunen...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.58,0:40:22.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I heard Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} scream!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.85,0:40:24.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It caught me by surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.26,0:40:27.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't blame her for being scared, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.13,0:40:30.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shunen! Did you—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.00,0:40:31.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.53,0:40:35.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't Ran who screamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.37,0:40:39.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was me!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.20,0:40:42.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not your fault you didn't hear me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.87,0:40:45.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were in here all night,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.21,0:40:47.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,surrounded by the thunderous roar of the water, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.88,0:40:51.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But his testimony won't hold as evidence, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.68,0:40:53.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's undeniable proof that you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.35,0:40:56.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then you're holding it right now, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.09,0:40:57.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This piece of wood?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.36,0:41:02.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By wiping the room off later, the killer could destroy the evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.16,0:41:04.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he couldn't do that with that piece of wood
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.16,0:41:06.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,since it went flying off.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.30,0:41:07.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.23,0:41:12.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the only thing the killer failed to recover!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.94,0:41:16.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I would bet my life as a detective
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.37,0:41:21.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that they're still on the tape stuck to that board...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.38,0:41:26.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I'm referring to your fingerprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.72,0:41:30.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Shunen came to this temple a year ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.16,0:41:32.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is the same trick as the one two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.59,0:41:33.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then the same person did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.59,0:41:35.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shunen couldn't have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.59,0:41:39.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The incident two years ago was probably the head priest's doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.83,0:41:42.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,using the exact same trick as this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.73,0:41:45.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cut on the drainboard was old,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.17,0:41:50.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he was the one most afraid to talk about the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.28,0:41:53.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And if my instincts are correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.95,0:42:00.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the late Chunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Shunen{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were probably brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.75,0:42:02.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.22,0:42:07.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Chunen was my genuine blood brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.43,0:42:10.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only natural that no one realized it...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.10,0:42:13.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To hide my origin, I came as a priest-in-training
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.16,0:42:16.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after studying at a distantly-related temple first.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.90,0:42:18.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, my purpose for coming to this temple
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.87,0:42:22.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was to find out the truth behind my brother's death
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.24,0:42:25.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and find the real culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.04,0:42:28.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I scoured the temple for half a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.45,0:42:32.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had the trick figured out, but I didn't know who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.82,0:42:36.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody wanted to talk about the incident, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.69,0:42:40.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I realized it when you came yesterday, Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.79,0:42:44.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew once I saw the head priest's strange attitude!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.73,0:42:49.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, I went to his room and found him drinking his night sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.97,0:42:52.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I pressed the issue, he told me about all sorts of things!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.60,0:42:55.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had no idea I was actually Chunen's younger brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.54,0:42:57.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason he killed my brother
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.54,0:43:01.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was because he didn't want him to take his granddaughter Kikuno{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.81,0:43:05.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who was to marry a successor to a big temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.28,0:43:10.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kikuno{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and my brother supposedly even agreed to elope together,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.56,0:43:13.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but that doesn't matter now...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.29,0:43:17.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, when I asked the head priest to give himself up, he—
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.96,0:43:24.30,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's no evidence left from what happened two years ago anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.30,0:43:30.24,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Besides, this temple has gained prestige thanks to that incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.24,0:43:36.38,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's known as the temple where the {\i1}Kiri Tengu{\i0} appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.38,0:43:39.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When he said that, I lost control of myself
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.05,0:43:43.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and strangled him to death with a belt in the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.92,0:43:48.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Just like he strangled my brother two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.96,0:43:50.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...with him on my back,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.76,0:43:53.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to leave marks to make it look like a hanging suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.60,0:43:57.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With his corpse at my feet, I had no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.94,0:44:00.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I would have to use the same trick he used two years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.77,0:44:03.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to hide the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.74,0:44:12.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too bad you didn't visit this temple two years ago, Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.82,0:44:17.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had, I would probably be...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.78,0:45:53.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You surprise me every single time, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.99,0:45:58.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea you knew that much about physics!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.56,0:46:02.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, like when you talked about Pascals or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.83,0:46:04.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Pascals"?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.26,0:46:07.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What they mean is—
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.27,0:46:08.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Paical" is Chinese alcohol...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.90,0:46:10.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Oscar" is from Takarazuka...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.60,0:46:12.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Rascal" is a kind of raccoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.47,0:46:16.67,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's a Pascal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.67,0:46:20.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you mean that TV magazine!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.75,0:46:23.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You dummy, that's "Telepal"!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.95,0:46:27.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And you only got the "al" right!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.85,0:46:32.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The weapon was a flower pot...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.35,0:46:34.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.68,0:46:37.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit butting in during our investigations!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.19,0:46:41.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The first issue is you, Dobashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.69,0:46:43.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then his wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.36,0:46:49.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears something hard hit it from below...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.63,0:46:52.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Only that person could've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.35,0:46:58.27,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.27,0:47:03.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Little Bird
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.65,0:47:05.45,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally a new school term next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.45,0:47:07.02,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be late!
